          @benforman- The thing is, Spurs didn't pass well against Arsenal because, for the most part, they weren't allowed to. City also press very well and high at home looking to win the ball back in the attacking third and I also doubt City will defend on the counter as bad as we did so I can't see the flow of the game being much different than that at the Emirates. Having said but Spurs have enough quality that they can exploit any space given and it's just a case of taking those chances. This will likely be akin to the Arsenal game, 30% or less posseion and a hell of a lot of defending but Pochettino is building a team both disciplined in defence and ruthless in attack so a point is not out of the question. Tactically, Pochettino sets up tight away from home so 3-0 likely wont happen. I'd look for Lamela to attack Mangala at every given opportunity cos as big a talent as Eliaquim is, he is still young and not yet used to the prem. I predict 2-1 to City and Dzeko MotM.
